		<statement delay="6.5" x="50" y="100" width="360" ><![CDATA[Food begins to spoil almost immediately it is harvested, taken from the sea or slaughtered. Good hygiene practices will reduce or eliminate spoilage.]]></statement>
		
		<statement delay="14.7" x="50" y="175" width="400" ><![CDATA[Bacteria, moulds, enzymes and yeasts result in spoilage.]]></statement>
		
		<statement delay="18.6" x="50" y="220" width="360" ><![CDATA[Poor hygiene, poor temperature control, unsuitable packaging and pest infestation speed up spoilage.]]></statement>
		
		<statement delay="32" x="50" y="280" width="300" ><![CDATA[Spoilage bacteria alter the appearance, taste, feel and smell of food:]]></statement>
		

